This paper deals with the problem of training temporal action proposal networks, which is a common module in action detection pipelines. The paper proposes a semi-supervised learning algorithm specifically designed for this task, which suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The datasets used in the experiments are video datasets, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of information retrieval techniques to evaluate the performance of the proposed method, which could also place it in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
